Serializable, DenseTensorMixin<CVector,CooCVector>, DenseVectorMixin<CVector,CooCVector,CMatrix,Field<Complex128>[],Complex128>, TensorBinaryOpsMixin<CVector,CVector>, TensorMixin<CVector,Field<Complex128>[],Complex128>, VectorMatrixOpsMixin<CVector,CMatrix,CMatrix>, VectorMixinOld<CVector,CMatrix,CMatrix,Field<Complex128>[],Complex128>
public class CVector extends DenseFieldVectorBase<CVector,CMatrix,CooCVector,Complex128>

A complex dense vector whose entries are Complex128's.

A vector is essentially equivalent to a rank 1 tensor but has some extended functionality and may have improved performance for some operations.

CVector's have mutable entries but a fixed size.

    • roundToZero

      public CVector roundToZero()
      Rounds values which are close to zero in absolute value to zero. If the tensor is complex, both the real and imaginary components will be rounded independently. By default, the values must be within Flag4jConstants.EPS_F64 of zero. To specify a threshold value see roundToZero(double).
      Returns:
      A copy of this tensor with rounded values.

    • roundToZero

      public CVector roundToZero(double threshold)
      Rounds values which are close to zero in absolute value to zero.
      Parameters:
      threshold - Threshold for rounding values to zero. That is, if a value in this matrix is less than the threshold in absolute value then it will be rounded to zero. This value must be non-negative.
      Returns:
      A copy of this matrix with rounded values.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If threshold is negative.
